## 🔄 Concurrency Scenarios

### Scenario 1: Sequential Access (No Contention)

```
Thread 1                          Thread 2
   │                                  │
   ├─ Lock & Update                   │
   │  (Fast: 20ms)                    │
   ├─ Commit                          │
   │                                  │
   │                                  ├─ Lock & Update
   │                                  │  (Fast: 20ms)
   │                                  └─ Commit
   │
Total Time: 40ms
```

**Result:** Both operations fast, no waiting

---

### Scenario 2: Concurrent Access (Contention)

```
Thread 1                          Thread 2
   │                                  │
   ├─ Lock (0ms)                      │
   │                                  ├─ Lock (waits)
   ├─ Update (20ms)                   │  ⏳ 20ms
   ├─ Commit (5ms)                    │  ⏳ 5ms
   │                                  ├─ Lock acquired (25ms wait)
   │                                  ├─ Update (20ms)
   │                                  └─ Commit (5ms)
   │
Thread 1: 25ms
Thread 2: 50ms (25ms wait + 25ms work)
```

**Result:** Thread 2 waits, but data is consistent

---

### Scenario 3: High Contention (Multiple Threads)

```
Thread 1    Thread 2    Thread 3    Thread 4
   │           │           │           │
   ├─ Lock     │           │           │
   │           ├─ Wait     │           │
   │           │           ├─ Wait     │
   │           │           │           ├─ Wait
   ├─ Done     │           │           │
   │           ├─ Lock     │           │
   │           │           │           │
   │           ├─ Done     │           │
   │           │           ├─ Lock     │
   │           │           │           │
   │           │           ├─ Done     │
   │           │           │           ├─ Lock
   │           │           │           │
   │           │           │           └─ Done

Thread 1: 25ms
Thread 2: 50ms
Thread 3: 75ms
Thread 4: 100ms
```

**Result:** Linear increase in wait time, but all succeed

