## ⚡ Performance Optimization

### 1. Keep Transactions Short

**❌ Bad:**
```java
@Transactional
public void processOrder() {
    // Lock acquired
    Inventory inv = repo.findByIdForUpdate(id);
    
    // Long operations while holding lock
    sendEmail();              // 2 seconds
    callPaymentGateway();     // 3 seconds
    generatePDF();            // 1 second
    
    inv.setQuantity(inv.getQuantity() - 10);
    // Lock held for 6+ seconds!
}
```

**✅ Good:**
```java
public void processOrder() {
    // Do heavy work OUTSIDE transaction
    sendEmail();
    callPaymentGateway();
    generatePDF();
    
    // Quick transaction
    updateInventory();  // < 100ms
}

@Transactional
private void updateInventory() {
    // Lock acquired
    Inventory inv = repo.findByIdForUpdate(id);
    inv.setQuantity(inv.getQuantity() - 10);
    // Lock released quickly
}
```

---

### 2. Use Proper Indexes

**Database Indexes:**
```sql
-- Composite index for fast lookups
CREATE INDEX idx_inventory_tenant_product 
ON inventory(tenant_id, product_id);

-- Speeds up FOR UPDATE queries
```

**Impact:**
- Without index: 500ms query time
- With index: 5ms query time
- **100x faster!**

