## 🧪 Testing Concurrency

### Test Setup

```java
@Test
void testConcurrentDeduction() {
    // Create thread pool
    ExecutorService executor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(2);
    
    // Synchronization
    CountDownLatch startLatch = new CountDownLatch(1);
    CountDownLatch endLatch = new CountDownLatch(2);
    
    // Thread 1
    executor.submit(() -> {
        startLatch.await();
        inventoryService.deductStock(productId, 30);
        endLatch.countDown();
    });
    
    // Thread 2
    executor.submit(() -> {
        startLatch.await();
        inventoryService.deductStock(productId, 40);
        endLatch.countDown();
    });
    
    // Start both threads
    startLatch.countDown();
    
    // Wait for completion
    endLatch.await(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
    
    // Verify
    Integer finalStock = inventoryService.getCurrentStock(productId);
    assertThat(finalStock).isEqualTo(30); // 100 - 30 - 40
}
```

### Test Results

**Without Locking:**
```
Run 1: Final stock = 60 ❌
Run 2: Final stock = 70 ❌
Run 3: Final stock = 30 ✅ (lucky!)
Run 4: Final stock = 60 ❌
```

**With Pessimistic Locking:**
```
Run 1: Final stock = 30 ✅
Run 2: Final stock = 30 ✅
Run 3: Final stock = 30 ✅
Run 4: Final stock = 30 ✅
... (100% consistent)
```

